cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG 

This paper proposes a machine learning approach to geolocate IP addresses using publicly accessible reverse DNS hostnames. As such, it is likely to fall under the categories of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of databases, which could place it under the category of databases (cs.DB). The machine learning aspect of the paper suggests that it could also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
